ow memories can be mobilised for political ends.  afunded by Schweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aElectronic books. 0aMemoryxPolitical aspectszAfrica. 0aMemoryxSocial aspectszAfrica. 4aAfrika. 4aErinnerungskultur. 4aGeschichte. 4aKollektives Gedächtnis. 4aPolitik. 7aHISTORY / Modern / General.2bisacsh  aAfrica.  acollective memory.  ahistorical remembrance.  amemory politics.1 aAndersen, Casper, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCharumbira, Ruramisai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFilippi, Natacha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodman, Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaji Ingiriis, Mohamed, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKunstmann, Rouven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMark-Thiesen, Cassandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMark-Thiesen, Cassandra, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMihatsch, Moritz A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMihatsch, Moritz, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSikes, Michelle M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSikes, Michelle, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStuder, Nina S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb2 aSchweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd